\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  C. echinus} (Bieb.) Hand.-Mazz.,{\i  Ann. Naturh. Mus.} ({\i Wien}){\b  23}: 197 (1909) ({\i C. scleranthum} Bieb.), from Anatolia, has been recorded from Turkey-in-Europe and Czechoslovakia, but probably only as a casual. It is like {\b 43} but differs in the pubescent stem 40-60(-130) cm, leaves whitish-arachnoid-tomentose beneath, the capitula solitary or in clusters of 2-3 on short branches, the outer involucral bracts with an ovate, whitish-fimbriate appendage and an apical spine 4-6 mm, and the corolla 17-20 mm.
