\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 44. C. acaule} Scop., {\i Annus Hist.-Nat.}{\b  2}: 62 (1769). Perennial, acaulescent or rarely with stem 5-15(-35) cm. Leaves herbaceous, undulate, oblong to oblong-lanceolate, pinnatisect; segments ovate to suborbicular, with 2-5 spinose-dentate lobes. Involucre 20-32 × (10-)16-25(-30) mm; bracts appressed, the vittae absent or indistinct. Corolla 23-35 mm, purple. Achenes 3-5 mm.{\i  From N. England and Estonia southwards to S. Spain, C. Jugoslavia and S.E. Russia.} Au Be Br Cz Da Ga Ge He Ho Hs It Ju No Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, E) Su.
