\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. C. mairei} Halácsy, {\i Consp. Fl. Graec., Suppl.} 59 (1908). Perennial 20-40 cm. Stem simple, leafy up to the apex. Leaves coriaceous, undulate, oblong, pinnatisect, pubescent above, sparsely arachnoid-lanate beneath; segments triangular, lobed, with strong spines 5-10 mm. Capitulum solitary, with 2-7 narrow, undulate-spiny subtending leaves shorter or rarely slightly longer than capitulum. Involucre 20-22 × 20-23 mm; bracts acute, erect, with pungent spine 1-5 mm; vittae absent. Corolla purple.{\i  Damp meadows. • S.C. Greece} ({\i Giona Oros}). Gr.
