\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 46. C. valentinum} Porta & Rigo, {\i Atti Accad. Agiati}{\b  9}: 38 (1892). Perennial 20-70 cm. Stem usually branched, leafless just below the apex. Leaves herbaceous, somewhat undulate, semiamplexicaul, sometimes shortly decurrent, oblong to oblong lanceolate, pinnatifid, with long flexuous hairs on both sides especially on the veins; segments triangular, lobed, with strong spines 4-8 mm. Capitula solitary, usually long-pedunculate, usually not subtended by leaves. Involucre 15-21(-24) × 13-20 mm; bracts acute, with conspicuous vittae and pungent spine 1-2 mm; outer erect; middle with erecto-patent apex. Corolla 23-26 mm, purple. Pappus 16-20 mm. •{\i  E. Spain} ({\i S.W. of Valencia}). Hs.
